Similarly, the formal and content errors of the invoice issued in the summer 2002 were swarmed with a foundation called Jobb Jövőért, later Együtt and Harmadik Éveredért.
The guesthouse in Badacsonytomaji had only three rooms, more than ten people could not sleep in it one night, yet one hundred and thirty guests were listed on the invoice.
However, the fillers of forms with rich imagination went too far even when they mentioned the documents of a company dedicated to hospitality - Pigal s.r.o., in which according to the information provided to the state prosecutor, the documents in the name Jobb Jövőért and Hoppá did not even appear.
