Finance Minister Henry Paulson stated about the outcome of the compromise: "The programme will work and it will be effective, but further action must be taken."
The written form of the package was published before the opening of Asian markets on Sunday at 8:00 p.m. Washington time (i.e. Monday at 2 a.m. Central European time), but it did not cause any special rise on the stock exchanges.
The House of Representatives will vote first on Monday, then it will be the Senate.
