The restriction essentially means that if the Ministry buys as part of the auction, a tax mark will be imposed on gold parachutes if the fallen bank directors are not sent straight to retirement.
In the event of a direct buyout of low-quality loans, the government will aggressively intervene to ensure that the money for leadership is not excessive.
It should be added that the already existing gold falling treaties will not change, the restriction concerns only new ones, which is intended to further stimulate participation in the programme.
"This is the first case in American history to have legal restrictions in force regarding the remuneration of CEOs," commented Chairman of the House of Representatives' Financial Services Committee, Democrat Barney Frank.
